\f1\fs40 \cf2 What is CouchDB - Introduction?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 Database management system facilitates mechanism for storing and retrieval of data. There are three major types of database management systems namely \uc0\u8722 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf0 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
RDBMS\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
NoSQL\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 \cb3 RDBMS\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 RDBMS stands for Relational Database Management System. RDBMS is the basis for SQL, and for all modern database systems such as MS SQL Server, IBM DB2, Oracle, MySQL, and Microsoft Access.\cb1 \
\cb3 A (RDBMS) is a database management system (DBMS) that is based on the relational model that was introduced by E. F. Codd.\cb1 \
\cb3 The data in RDBMS is stored in database objects known astables. The table is a collection of associated data entries and it contains columns and rows. It will store structured data only.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 \cb3 NoSQL Databases\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 A NoSQL database (also called as Not Only SQL) is a database that facilittaes a mechanism for storing and retrieving of data other than the tabular relations employed in relational databases. These databases are schema-free, support easy replication, have simple API, eventually consistent, and have ability to handle large amounts of data (big data).\cb1 \
\cb3 The main objective of a NoSQL database is to have the below \uc0\u8722 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf0 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Simplicity of design,\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Horizontal scaling, and\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Finer control over availability.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 NoSQL databases will use different data structures in comparision to relational databases. It makes some operations faster in NoSQL. The suitability of a given NoSQL database merely depends on the problem it should solve. These databases will store both structured data and unstructured data such as audio files, video files, documents, etc. These NoSQL databases are divided into three types and they are explained in the following sections.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 \cb3 Key-value Store
\b0  \uc0\u8722  These databases are designed for storing the data in key-value pairs and these databases wont have any schema. In these databases, each data value contains an indexed key and a value for that key.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Below are the examples :\cb1 \
\cb3 BerkeleyDB, Cassandra, DynamoDB, Riak.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 \cb3 Column Store
\b0 \uc0\u8722  In these databases, data is stored in cells grouped in columns of data, and these columns are in turn grouped into Column families. These column families can consists of number of columns.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Below are the examples :\cb1 \
\cb3 BigTable, HBase, and HyperTable.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 \cb3 Document Store
\b0  \uc0\u8722  These are the databases developed on the basic idea of key-value stores where "documents"consists of more complex data. Here, every document is assigned a unique key, which is used for retrieving the document. These are designed for storing, retrieving, and managing document-oriented information, also called as semi-structured data.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Below are the examples :\cb1 \
\cb3 CouchDB and MongoDB.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 \cb3 What is CouchDB?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 CouchDB is an open source database and it was developed by Apache software foundation. The mainemphasis is on the simplicity of use, embracing the web. It is a NoSQL document store database.\cb1 \
\cb3 It employes JSON, to store data (documents), java script as its query language for transforming the documents, http protocol for api for accessing the documents, query the indices with the web browser. CouchDB is a multi master application released in 2005 and it became an apache project in 2008.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 \cb3 Why CouchDB?\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf0 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
CouchDB have an HTTP-based REST API, which assists to interact with the DB easily. And the easy structure of HTTP resources and methods (GET, PUT, DELETE) are simple to understand and make use of if.\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
As we store data in the flexible document-based structure, there is no necessity to botherregarding the structure of the data.\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Users are facilitated with powerful data mapping, which permits querying, combining, and filtering of the information.\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
CouchDB facilitatessimple-to-use replication, employing which you can copy, share, and synchronize the data between databases and machines.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 \cb3 What is Data Model?\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf0 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Database is the outermost data structure/container in CouchDB.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Each database is a group of independent documents.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Each document will maintains its own data and self-contained schema.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Document metadata consists of revision information, which makes it feasible to combine the differences occurred while the databases were disconnected.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
CouchDB implements multi version concurrency control, to keep away the need to lock the database field during writes.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 \cb3 What are the futures of CouchDB?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 Document Storage
\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf0 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
CouchDB is a document storage NoSQL database. Documents are the major unit of data, every field is uniquely named and consists of values of diffeent data types like text, number, Boolean, lists, etc... In these documents there is no set limit to text size or element count.\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
CouchDB facilitates an API called RESTful HTTP API for the purpose of reading and updating (add, edit, delete) database documents.\cb1 \
