\fs36 \cf0 \cb3 ACID Properties\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 The CouchDB file layout and commitment system features all the ACID properties.\cb1 \
\cb3 Once the data is entered in to the disc it will not be overwritten. Document updates (add, edit, delete) will follow Atomicity, i.e., they will be saved completely or not saved at all. The database will not have any partially saved or edited documents.\cb1 \
\cb3 Most of these update are serialized and any number of clients can read a document without being waiting and also without being interrupted.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 \cb3 Compaction
\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Compaction is an operation to avail extra disc space for the database by discarding unused data. While performing compaction operation on a given file, a file with the extension. Compaction is created and all the active/actual data is copied (cloned) to that file, when the copying process is completed then the old file is removed. The database remains online during the compaction and all updates and reads are permitted to finish successfully.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 \cb3 Views
\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Data in CouchDB is stored in semi-structured documents that are adaptable with individual implicit structures, but it is aneasy document model for data storing and sharing. If we wish to see our data in various ways, we require a way to filter, organize and report on data that hasn\'92t been decomposed into tables.\cb1 \
\cb3 For solving this problem, CouchDB facilitates a view model. Views are the method of aggregating and reporting on the documents in a database, and are built on-demand to aggregate, join and report on database documents. As views are built dynamically and don\'92t affect the underlying document, you may have various view representations of the same data as you wish.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

