\f1\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 What is CouchDB - Creating a Document?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 Documents are CouchDB\'92s central data structure. Database Contents will be stored in the form of Documents rather than of tables. You can create these documents with cURL utility facilitated by CouchDB, and also the Futon. This chapter explains the ways for creating a document in a database.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 \cb3 Each document in CouchDB will have a unique ID. You can select your own ID that must be in the form of a string. Usually, UUID (Universally Unique IDentifier) is employed, which are random numbers that will have very least chances of creating a duplicate. These are preferred in order to avert collisions.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

