\cf0 \cb3 Below are some major points to be noted during updating a document.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls16\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf0 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The URL we send in the request consisting of database name and the document id.\cb1 \
\ls16\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Updating an existing document is similar to as updating the complete document. You cannot add a field to a document that is existing. You can only write an entirely new version of the document into the database with the same document ID.\cb1 \
\ls16\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
We need to supply the revision number as a part of the JSON request.\cb1 \
\ls16\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
In return JSON consists of the success message, the ID of the document that was being updated, and the new revision information. If you wish to update the new version of the document, you requireto quote this latest revision number.\cb1 \
