\f1\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 How to Attach Files with cURL?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs30 \cf0 \cb3 You can also attach files to CouchDB, similarly you do in email. The file consists of metadata such as name and includes its MIME type, and the number of bytes the attachment consists of. For attaching files to a document you need to send PUT request to the server.\cb1 \
\cb3 Below is the syntax for attaching files to the document \'96\cb1 \
\
\cb3 x\cb1 \
\
\
\cb3 \'a0\cb1 \
